channel.description:

Support our community! Click now to open their [Soundcloud](https://soundcloud.com/sofus-agervig-351033928/tracks).
_There's **less than 10 spots** available if you want to [put yourself forward](https://disco.auxy.co/t/forum-member-of-the-week-who-wants-to-be-involved/5518) to be featured in the forum this year._

item.title: Forum Member of the Week - 01: SUFOS
item.dc:creator: LittleSpikes
item.description:
What a nice user selection to start this weekly feedback thread.

Overall, I like your style of composing.
As I left some comment in SC, I like some chord you made, and cool pitch bending. you are also good at making chill drops. nice work

If I could give an advice, it would be probably about melody line.
The melodies are a little bit too repetitive in your track. I guess.
Maybe, these would help you to avoid repetitiveness

  • Change pitch from middle or last part of the track (so you can make a climax in a melody while avoiding repetitiveness)
  • Try multiple main melody lines. if you make 2 main melodies in general, make it 3. if it’s 3, make it 4.

Look forward to your next one!

Read full topic
